Hi there! I’m trying to customize the hover color of a HubSpot button CTA. I’ve assigned in the custom CSS class “applycta” in HubSpot and added the following code to the website’s style sheet, but it doesn’t seem to be working. Does anyone know how to properly tweak this code to work? Here’s the page it’s on: <https://www.mentorworks.ca/government-funding/research-development/alberta-innovates-accelerating-innovations-into-care/>

CSS code on the site:
.applycta:hover {
  background-color: #C2571D !important;
}
